Shit.

253
00:15:44.210 --> 00:15:47.216
Why is there a tree
in the middle of the road?

254
00:15:47.300 --> 00:15:49.592
Must've gotten knocked down
in a storm or something.

255
00:15:50.826 --> 00:15:52.731
Well. that's a pretty
selective storm.

256
00:16:00.705 --> 00:16:03.102
Well. there was an exit
about a mile back.

257
00:16:03.186 --> 00:16:05.365
I think we're gonna
have to circle around.

258
00:16:05.449 --> 00:16:08.585
Maybe we can push
it with the RV.

259
00:16:08.669 --> 00:16:10.749
I don't think that's
gonna work. buddy.

260
00:16:13.147 --> 00:16:14.661
Dad. get me up.

261
00:16:15.589 --> 00:16:18.068
Come on. [Grunting]

262
00:16:22.335 --> 00:16:26.732
[Crows caw]

263
00:16:28.334 --> 00:16:33.417
[More crows caw]

264
00:16:40.397 --> 00:16:45.349
[Crows continue
to caw]

265
00:16:49.275 --> 00:16:51.051
What are
they doing?

266
00:16:52.359 --> 00:16:54.190
Can we just
leave. please?

267
00:16:54.367 --> 00:16:56.285
Yeah. Come on.

268
00:16:56.369 --> 00:16:57.678
Jim!

269
00:16:57.762 --> 00:17:00.725
[Crows continue
to caw]

270
00:17:00.809 --> 00:17:02.596
- Yeah.
- Come on. buddy.

271
00:17:02.680 --> 00:17:07.632
[Crows continue
to caw]

272
00:17:13.212 --> 00:17:18.208
[People talking
indistinctly]

273
00:17:22.874 --> 00:17:25.227
We have an
arrangement. Sheriff.

274
00:17:25.311 --> 00:17:27.403
You don't come here.

275
00:17:27.487 --> 00:17:29.437
I came to see my
son. Donna.

276
00:17:32.318 --> 00:17:34.094
Please.

277
00:17:36.322 --> 00:17:37.574
Come on in. then.

278
00:17:41.850 --> 00:17:46.802
[Acoustic guitar
plays softly]

279
00:18:15.796 --> 00:18:17.048
What?

280
00:18:18.799 --> 00:18:21.675
You're like a poem.
You know that?

281
00:18:21.759 --> 00:18:23.686
You make everything
around you beautiful.

282
00:18:23.771 --> 00:18:25.023
[Chuckling]

283
00:18:27.199 --> 00:18:28.452
Even this place.

284
00:18:38.950 --> 00:18:41.260
[Surprised]
Sheriff Stevens.

285
00:18:41.344 --> 00:18:42.522
[Laughing]

286
00:18:42.606 --> 00:18:44.219
Hello. Fatima.

287
00:18:44.303 --> 00:18:46.265
You should come by
more often.

288
00:18:46.349 --> 00:18:49.169
Yeah. [Laughing] Yeah.

289
00:18:53.312 --> 00:18:55.827
I will give
you boys a minute.

290
00:19:01.842 --> 00:19:04.488
I mean. she doesn't
change. does she?

291
00:19:05.934 --> 00:19:07.230
What are
you doing here?

292
00:19:08.240 --> 00:19:10.886
Yeah. Well. uh...

293
00:19:15.115 --> 00:19:17.296
we lost a couple
people last night.

294
00:19:17.380 --> 00:19:18.632
Oh. did we?

295
00:19:20.136 --> 00:19:22.294
And how exactly
did we lose them?

296
00:19:23.332 --> 00:19:27.153
Lauren Pratt and
her little girl. Meagan.

297
00:19:29.087 --> 00:19:31.259
- Lauren was the...
- Yeah. I know who Lauren is.

298
00:19:35.093 --> 00:19:39.622
It might be nice if you
came to the service.

299
00:19:39.706 --> 00:19:41.404
paid your respects.

300
00:19:42.144 --> 00:19:44.466
Look. I'm a little
busy. so if that's all...

301
00:19:45.886 --> 00:19:47.227
That's all.

302
00:19:49.603 --> 00:19:51.303
That's all.

303
00:19:51.544 --> 00:19:52.796
I thought I...

304
00:19:55.984 --> 00:19:57.889
I'll show
myself out.

305
00:20:06.701 --> 00:20:09.695
- Fatima.
- Bye.

306
00:20:17.483 --> 00:20:21.142
[Static sounds in
earphones]

307
00:20:21.226 --> 00:20:24.264
Can we go back to some place that
resembles civilization?

308
00:20:26.623 --> 00:20:28.758
I mean. maybe we missed
the sign for the highway?

309
00:20:28.842 --> 00:20:30.673
We didn't miss
the sign.

310
00:20:30.757 --> 00:20:34.242
[Son] Dad? Dad. how come
those crows were doing that?

311
00:20:34.326 --> 00:20:35.461
I don't know. buddy.

312
00:20:35.545 --> 00:20:37.637
Sometimes. crows do
funny things.

313
00:20:37.721 --> 00:20:39.682
Ca-caw! Ca-caw!

314
00:20:39.766 --> 00:20:42.630
[Laughing]

315
00:20:47.035 --> 00:20:49.083
Are you sure we're going in
the right direction?

316
00:20:49.167 --> 00:20:51.303
I mean. I... I don't see
the highway anymore.

317
00:20:51.387 --> 00:20:52.727
Do you have
cell reception?

318
00:20:54.694 --> 00:20:56.308
- No.
- I don't know.

319
00:20:56.392 --> 00:20:57.764
At some point.
this has to...

320
00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:05.000
[Gentle music plays]

321
00:21:09.579 --> 00:21:14.618
[Music turns ominous]

322
00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:17.447
What the...

323
00:21:22.635 --> 00:21:24.585
Why are all the tires flat?

324
00:21:29.903 --> 00:21:34.955
And so. we commit to the earth
Lauren and Meagan Pratt.

325
00:21:35.039 --> 00:21:38.785
May the life they know
beyond this world be kinder.

326
00:21:38.869 --> 00:21:41.962
and may the mysteries of
their time here be solved.

327
00:21:42.046 --> 00:21:44.051
For the peace we shall
know in the kingdom of God

328
00:21:44.135 --> 00:21:47.912
is certain.
and in that peace...

329
00:21:58.062 --> 00:22:00.589
Why are they
looking at us?

330
00:22:00.673 --> 00:22:01.764
Shit.

331
00:22:01.848 --> 00:22:06.030
[People talking
indistinctly]

332
00:22:06.114 --> 00:22:08.641
Um. and
in that peace...

333
00:22:08.725 --> 00:22:11.600
[Father clearing throat]
And in that peace.

334
00:22:11.684 --> 00:22:14.473
we can be sure Lauren and
Meagan now reside.

335
00:22:14.557 --> 00:22:16.518
- Hey. Lock the doors.
- Jim. Jim. Jim.

336
00:22:16.602 --> 00:22:17.737
- That's a funeral!
- Dad.

337
00:22:17.821 --> 00:22:19.233
- I'll be okay.
- [Julie] Dad.

338
00:22:20.998 --> 00:22:22.742
[Lock clicks]

339
00:22:22.826 --> 00:22:26.386
Ashes to ashes.
dust to dust.

340
00:22:27.961 --> 00:22:29.519
Alright. Now...

341
00:22:31.226 --> 00:22:33.654
you all remember what it
was like for you.

342
00:22:34.490 --> 00:22:36.103
Just leave
these people be.

343
00:22:36.187 --> 00:22:39.715
Kenny and I'll
handle it. Okay?

344
00:22:39.799 --> 00:22:40.716
Amen.

345
00:22:40.800 --> 00:22:42.675
[Townspeople]
Amen.

346
00:22:42.759 --> 00:22:44.011
May they go
with God.

347
00:22:50.593 --> 00:22:52.455
Excuse me. Could you
tell me where. uh...

348
00:22:56.251 --> 00:22:59.201
Hey. I was wondering if you
could tell me where. uh...

349
00:23:01.212 --> 00:23:03.870
Well. they seem like
a cheery group.

350
00:23:03.954 --> 00:23:06.046
What's going on?

351
00:23:06.130 --> 00:23:07.787
It's okay.

352
00:23:07.871 --> 00:23:09.441
Can I help you?

353
00:23:09.525 --> 00:23:11.138
Oh. yeah.

354
00:23:11.222 --> 00:23:13.053
Sorry to interrupt
your service.

355
00:23:13.137 --> 00:23:14.576
No. Not a problem.

356
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:15.838
We were
just wrapping up.

357
00:23:15.922 --> 00:23:17.666
Well. we got on a
detour off the highway.

358
00:23:17.750 --> 00:23:19.625
and. uh. cell service
around here is...

359
00:23:19.709 --> 00:23:21.092
Got your family
with you?

360
00:23:24.583 --> 00:23:25.835
Yeah.

361
00:23:29.806 --> 00:23:31.115
I was wondering if you could
point me

362
00:23:31.199 --> 00:23:33.540
in the direction of the highway.

363
00:23:35.290 --> 00:23:36.772
Yeah. You just. uh...

364
00:23:36.856 --> 00:23:39.688
You just keep on following
the road right up that hill.

365
00:23:39.772 --> 00:23:41.504
right where you were
going. and. uh...

366
00:23:42.471 --> 00:23:43.723
you'll see.

367
00:23:47.780 --> 00:23:50.438
Again. apologies.

368
00:23:50.522 --> 00:23:51.774
Not a problem.

369
00:24:01.968 --> 00:24:03.059
Unlock the door.

370
00:24:03.143 --> 00:24:04.395
Go.

371
00:24:07.887 --> 00:24:09.892
- What did he say?
- [Engine starts]

372
00:24:09.976 --> 00:24:11.981
Just keep going up the road
and we'll find it.

373
00:24:12.065 --> 00:24:17.148
[Ominous
music plays]

374
00:24:39.179 --> 00:24:41.620
How far did he say
the highway was?

375
00:24:41.704 --> 00:24:44.001
He didn't. He just said.
"Stay on the road."

376
00:24:47.013 --> 00:24:48.714
Hey!

377
00:24:48.798 --> 00:24:51.891
You know there's a name for
what those crows did back there.

378
00:24:51.975 --> 00:24:54.720
when they all. like. got
in a group like that?

379
00:24:54.804 --> 00:24:56.156
It's called
a murder.

380
00:24:56.240 --> 00:24:58.724
What? No. it's not.

381
00:24:58.808 --> 00:25:01.117
Yeah. it is. It's called
a murder of crows.

382
00:25:01.201 --> 00:25:02.902
'Cause when
they gather like that.

383
00:25:02.986 --> 00:25:04.599
it means they're
looking for a victim.

384
00:25:04.683 --> 00:25:05.731
And if you
see them doing it.

385
00:25:05.815 --> 00:25:07.254
then you're the one
they murder.

386
00:25:07.338 --> 00:25:09.561
Shut up.
You're making that up.

387
00:25:09.645 --> 00:25:11.911
I'm not.
Once they see you.

388
00:25:11.995 --> 00:25:14.043
they won't stop
hunting you.

389
00:25:14.127 --> 00:25:15.567
And one night when
you're sleeping.

390
00:25:15.651 --> 00:25:18.352
they'll come into your room and
crawl under your sheets.

391
00:25:18.436 --> 00:25:19.919
and they'll peck
at your face...

392
00:25:20.003 --> 00:25:21.050
- Stop it!
- And your eyes...

393
00:25:21.134 --> 00:25:22.095
- Stop it!
- -and your ears.

394
00:25:22.179 --> 00:25:24.793
Stop it!
Mom. tell her to stop!

395
00:25:24.877 --> 00:25:26.870
Goddamn it. Julie!
Knock it off!

396
00:25:28.446 --> 00:25:30.570
[Whispering]
You're such a baby.

397
00:25:31.841 --> 00:25:33.877
[Exhaling]

398
00:25:39.979 --> 00:25:41.231
Honey. you know what?

399
00:25:43.069 --> 00:25:44.801
I don't think those
were even crows.

400
00:25:45.985 --> 00:25:47.642
They looked like...

401
00:25:47.726 --> 00:25:49.688
They looked like
ravens to me.

402
00:25:49.772 --> 00:25:51.864
and you know what a group
of ravens are called?

403
00:25:53.906 --> 00:25:55.171
An unkindness.

404
00:25:55.255 --> 00:25:56.596
[Sighing]

405
00:25:59.129 --> 00:26:01.656
An unkindness of ravens.

406
00:26:01.740 --> 00:26:03.179
That doesn't sound
that bad. huh?

407
00:26:03.263 --> 00:26:04.515
No.

408
00:26:05.788 --> 00:26:07.040
[Sighing]

409
00:26:10.096 --> 00:26:13.886
Wait. wait. wait.
Did we turn somewhere?

410
00:26:13.970 --> 00:26:15.222
No. I just...

411
00:26:21.281 --> 00:26:23.144
Oh. this can't be
the same place.

412
00:26:24.502 --> 00:26:26.518
This is
getting really creepy.

413
00:26:26.603 --> 00:26:31.164
[Ominous music
playing]

414
00:26:31.814 --> 00:26:33.066
Excuse me.

415
00:26:34.643 --> 00:26:37.637
We're trying to get back onto
the highway. Could you...

416
00:26:40.910 --> 00:26:42.162
Are you kidding me?

417
00:26:44.522 --> 00:26:46.907
Let's just go. We... we
probably missed the turn.

418
00:27:01.713 --> 00:27:02.965
There you are.

419
00:27:03.889 --> 00:27:06.068
Just heading back down
to the barn.

420
00:27:06.152 --> 00:27:07.940
Those new people still
driving around. huh?

421
00:27:08.024 --> 00:27:09.756
It's the worst part.

422
00:27:10.461 --> 00:27:11.944
When you still expect
to find the road

423
00:27:12.028 --> 00:27:13.281
that takes you home.

424
00:27:14.334 --> 00:27:15.805
It's the part that's cruel.

425
00:27:16.728 --> 00:27:17.980
Hey. you okay?

426
00:27:18.904 --> 00:27:20.996
I'm fine.

427
00:27:21.080 --> 00:27:22.563
You're a
good brother.

428
00:27:22.647 --> 00:27:25.436
Now. get. Those animals
aren't gonna feed themselves.

429
00:27:25.520 --> 00:27:27.332
It'd be cool if
they did. though. right?

430
00:27:29.132 --> 00:27:30.136
I'll be back
in a bit.

431
00:27:30.220 --> 00:27:35.303
[Ominous music plays]

432
00:27:44.495 --> 00:27:47.109
Maybe it's... Maybe it's
more of. like. um...

433
00:27:47.193 --> 00:27:48.676
What's that...
What's that word?

434
00:27:48.760 --> 00:27:50.069
Like. a switchback.

435
00:27:50.153 --> 00:27:51.810
You know what I'm
talking about?

436
00:27:51.894 --> 00:27:53.202
Like. like. you
merge getting on.

437
00:27:53.286 --> 00:27:55.814
but then to get back. you'd
almost have to do. like.

438
00:27:55.898 --> 00:27:57.903
a U-turn to get back on
the original road.

439
00:27:57.987 --> 00:28:00.122
I would have noticed if we'd
merged with another road.

440
00:28:00.206 --> 00:28:01.863
Well. you obviously
didn't. Jim.

441
00:28:01.947 --> 00:28:03.169
because we're
driving in circles.

442
00:28:03.253 --> 00:28:04.344
Just drive slow.

443
00:28:04.428 --> 00:28:05.855
I'm driving slow.

444
00:28:10.478 --> 00:28:12.091
You have
to drive slow!

445
00:28:12.175 --> 00:28:13.353
Jim. we're gonna
pass it again!

446
00:28:13.437 --> 00:28:15.050
Pass what. Tabitha?

447
00:28:15.134 --> 00:28:17.966
What? Switchback?
Where is it?

448
00:28:18.050 --> 00:28:19.302
Show it to me.

449
00:28:21.358 --> 00:28:23.885
I'm... I'm driving 20
miles an hour. alright?

450
00:28:23.969 --> 00:28:25.477
I can't drive any...

451
00:28:27.930 --> 00:28:29.182
Goddamn it.

452
00:28:34.414 --> 00:28:36.376
[Tabitha] No. no. no. no.
This is impossible.

453
00:28:36.460 --> 00:28:38.758
We didn't go in
a circle that time.

454
00:28:40.029 --> 00:28:41.468
You drove out
this way.

455
00:28:41.552 --> 00:28:43.731
How did we
get back here?

456
00:28:43.815 --> 00:28:48.388
No. No. This... No.

457
00:28:48.472 --> 00:28:50.334
[Engine revving]

458
00:29:06.446 --> 00:29:07.886
You think
they're ready?

459
00:29:07.970 --> 00:29:09.757
Go ahead.
Get the strip.

460
00:29:09.841 --> 00:29:14.458
[Crows cawing]

461
00:29:14.542 --> 00:29:19.842
[Suspenseful
music playing]

462
00:29:20.591 --> 00:29:22.291
[Tabitha] How is this possible?

463
00:29:22.375 --> 00:29:24.511
The same road can't go
in a circle one time

464
00:29:24.595 --> 00:29:26.339
and then go in a...

465
00:29:26.423 --> 00:29:28.285
We're on the same
fucking road!

466
00:29:33.865 --> 00:29:34.956
Oh. my God. Jim.

467
00:29:35.040 --> 00:29:37.089
We should ask them.
Maybe they know.

468
00:29:37.173 --> 00:29:38.177
[Tires squealing]

469
00:29:38.261 --> 00:29:39.744
- [Horn honking]
- Oh!

470
00:29:39.828 --> 00:29:40.745
Oh. my God!

471
00:29:40.829 --> 00:29:42.224
[Crashing]

472
00:29:42.308 --> 00:29:43.560
[Screaming]

473
00:29:50.882 --> 00:29:53.006
No. [Groaning]

474
00:29:54.016 --> 00:29:56.238
No. no. no. no!

475
00:29:56.322 --> 00:29:58.620
[Banging] No. no. no!

476
00:30:01.589 --> 00:30:05.378
Tabby? Come here. baby.

477
00:30:05.462 --> 00:30:08.903
Tabby? Tabby.
[Grunting]

478
00:30:08.987 --> 00:30:10.296
I need to hear from you
both back there.

479
00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:12.603
[Julie grunting]

480
00:30:12.687 --> 00:30:15.214
Julie? Julie. I need
you to look at me.

481
00:30:15.298 --> 00:30:16.550
Are you okay?

482
00:30:18.170 --> 00:30:20.524
Yeah. uh. uh. yeah.
I think... I think so.

483
00:30:20.608 --> 00:30:22.351
I just banged my back.

484
00:30:22.435 --> 00:30:25.267
Ethan?
Can you hear me?

485
00:30:25.351 --> 00:30:27.831
Ethan? Ethan!

486
00:30:28.777 --> 00:30:30.652
[Strained]
I'm stuck.

487
00:30:35.361 --> 00:30:37.497
[Banging]

488
00:30:37.581 --> 00:30:40.500
[Jim grunting]

489
00:30:40.584 --> 00:30:45.623
[Rattling. grunting]

490
00:30:48.723 --> 00:30:51.206
Tabitha. baby.
come here.

491
00:30:51.605 --> 00:30:53.567
- Come here. honey.
- [Julie] What's wrong with Mom?

492
00:30:53.651 --> 00:30:55.003
Is... is she okay?

493
00:30:55.087 --> 00:30:57.223
- [Jim] She's gonna be fine.
- [Julie grunts]

494
00:30:57.307 --> 00:30:58.878
We're all
gonna be fine.

495
00:30:58.963 --> 00:31:01.229
I'm gonna get
us out of here.

496
00:31:01.314 --> 00:31:03.450
- We all just got to...
- [Metal creaking]

497
00:31:03.859 --> 00:31:05.156
...hold still.

498
00:31:15.128 --> 00:31:16.380
[Grunting]

499
00:31:20.286 --> 00:31:22.605
[Gagging]

500
00:31:22.690 --> 00:31:24.813
[Coughing]

501
00:31:33.433 --> 00:31:35.787
Make sure you
cover it real well.

502
00:31:35.871 --> 00:31:39.486
Last thing we need is a goddamn
RV barreling through town.

503
00:31:39.570 --> 00:31:42.097
They had. uh.
Arizona plates.

504
00:31:42.181 --> 00:31:43.185
You ever been
to Arizona?

505
00:31:43.269 --> 00:31:45.057
[Man] Hey!

506
00:31:45.141 --> 00:31:47.320
- Hey. we need help!
- [Sheriff] What the...

507
00:31:47.404 --> 00:31:49.278
- [Kenny] Was that guy in the RV?
- [Sheriff] No.

508
00:31:49.362 --> 00:31:50.671
[Man] There's
been an accident.

509
00:31:50.755 --> 00:31:52.499
- [Sheriff] What?
- It's... it's really bad.

510
00:31:52.583 --> 00:31:53.979
Oh. okay.
How far up the road?

511
00:31:54.063 --> 00:31:55.763
- Um...
- Okay. Okay.

